Sherbie the Love Nug is a great day time option, as this strain is a sativa leaning hybrid. With top terpenes Limonene, Caryophyllene, and Linalool, this strain may offer patients mood elevation, and gentle relaxation.  This strain may also be a good option for those looking to manage their anxiety. Sherbie the Love Nug has strong scents of citrus cleaner and a bit of sweetness on the backend.  
-
Limonene is a terpene found in the rinds of citrus fruits, bergamot, and peppermint. This terpene has a citrusy and fruity aroma and flavor profile. Limonene may cause an uplift in mood, may help reduce stress, and promote relaxation. 
-
Beta-Caryophyllene is another terpene commonly found in a wide range of cannabis strains. This terpene is found in things like rosemary, oregano, and peppercorns, and has a peppery-spicy type of flavor. Beta-caryophyllene may assist with pain management and relaxation without the “couch lock” feeling. 
-
Linalool is commonly known for being present in lavender plants. This terpene has a sweet & floral scent and flavor profile. Using medical marijuana that has elevated levels of linalool may offer users calming effects, may assist in reducing anxious thoughts and feelings, and may help calm the body to improve quality of sleep.

Berry Gelatoe is a hybrid strain that offers notes of sweet fruit, cheese funk, and berries. This strain’s buds are deep green and absolutely gorgeous. With top terpenes being Linalool, Limonene, and Myrcene, patients can expect a wide range of effects associated with this strain. Patients struggling with anxiety and depression may find comfort when using Berry Gelatoe. This strain may also assist those who are combating pain management. 
-
Linalool is commonly known for being present in lavender plants. This terpene has a sweet & floral scent and flavor profile. Using medical marijuana that has elevated levels of linalool may offer users calming effects, may assist in reducing anxious thoughts and feelings, and may help calm the body to improve quality of sleep. 
-
Limonene is a terpene found in the rinds of citrus fruits, bergamot, and peppermint. This terpene has a citrusy and fruity aroma and flavor profile. Limonene may cause an uplift in mood, may help reduce stress, and promote relaxation. 
-
Myrcene is the most abundant terpene found in cannabis and can be found in almost all cannabis strains to some degree. This terpene is found in things such as mangoes, lemongrass, thyme, and hops. This fruity, musky, mildly herbaceous terpene offers users overall body relaxation, cerebral euphoria, and may assist in pain management.

Blueberry Sour is a well-balanced hybrid with top terpenes Linalool, Limonene, and Myrcene. Buds from this plant are so dark they’re almost black and completely covered in trichomes, making them glisten beautifully! With scents of sweet fruit along with mild blueberry notes, this strain smells just as good as it looks. Effects from Blueberry Sour may include euphoria, along with helping manage stress, depression and anxiety. This hybrid strain is well suited for use any time of day or night. 
-
Linalool is commonly known for being present in lavender plants. This terpene has a sweet & floral scent and flavor profile. Using medical marijuana that has elevated levels of linalool may offer users calming effects, may assist in reducing anxious thoughts and feelings, and may help calm the body to improve quality of sleep. 
-
Limonene is a terpene found in the rinds of citrus fruits, bergamot, and peppermint. This terpene has a citrusy and fruity aroma and flavor profile. Limonene may cause an uplift in mood, may help reduce stress, and promote relaxation. 
-
Myrcene is the most abundant terpene found in cannabis and can be found in almost all cannabis strains to some degree. This terpene is found in things such as mangoes, lemongrass, thyme, and hops. This fruity, musky, mildly herbaceous terpene offers users overall body relaxation, cerebral euphoria, and may assist in pain management.
